{
  "texts": [
    "This is required for statistical studies, e.g.",
    "flux ratio or light curve analysis, but does not need to be the case for high magnification events, which are usually dominated by a single caustic crossing that has well-defined, universal properties (Fluke and Webster 1999).",
    "That is, if the source is placed in these locations it will overlap with itself.",
    "This applies equally to tracks across maps.",
    "For practical purposes, the full extent of the source could be replaced by some fraction of its half-light radius."
  ]
}